  *  Press left mouse button for increase W, H, X, Y and Level number.

  *  Press right mouse button for decrease W, H, X, Y and Level number.

  *  Press both mouse buttons for clear current level window.

  *  Press right mouse button in the editor window for clear single brick.

  *  Extras can be assigned only bricks found on the first row.

  *  Last six bricks of second row are indestructible bricks.

  *  For assigning a special feature to a brick, move your mouse
     upon a brick and press one of the following keys.

     HELP ... Shows help page

     X ...... Extra life                K ...... Kills a life

     L ...... Laser                     G ...... Glue feature

     N ...... Go to next level          I ...... Reverses ball direction

     M ...... Missile                   O ...... Changes ball size

     E ...... Enlarges size of bat      C ...... Auto control

     R ...... Reduces size of bat       H ...... Destructive balls
     
     S ...... Faster ball speed         P ...... Freezer

     F ...... Slower ball speed         # ...... Disables all extras

     B ...... Adds extra ball           ? ...... Random feature


 -----------
   NOTICE:
 -----------
  *  Only requirement of this game is a 80 column 'SYSTEM-CONFIGURATION'
 file on the boot disc. If boot disc not contains a 'SYSTEM-CONFIGURATION'
 file (on DEVS or ROOT directory), Amiga sets default font to Topaz-9 and 
 opens a 60 column Workbench screen. That corrupts game design.

  *  Faster computers (68020+) gives better results (faster gameplay).


